      "content": "\"stuck with it\"... i don't know if that's the right word. stuck implies there's still something worth keeping, just trapped. but there isn't. it's just heaviness. it's like carrying around a corpse that won't stay buried. what's the point of just continuing the habit if there's no one actually home anymore?",
